        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> It's important to note that you never actually lose aggro on the mob (unless the aggro was allready lost via FD).  You are FD so the mob dosn't know about you and the thing is that you stand up and invis before he actually has time to re-aggro so he dosn't 'know' you stood up.  If you broke invis, he'd run right back at ya just like if you stood up and diddn't invis cuz then he actually gets a chance to see you're not dead.  So, the pre-nerf CoS never actually breaks aggro in any situation.  Just helps you hide from aggro mobs that don't see invis.</P><P>Try it out if you haven't.  Go to the Grey and aggro a rockfiend.  FD and then stand up and click your circlet instantly after.  If you do it right, of cource, he won't be beating on you.  Now, walk back well out of his normal aggro radius (But not halfway across the zone.  Stay kinda close.  Just not TOO close.).  Click off invis.  He'll run right at you.  If you did end up running halfway across the zone, just run back and run by him without invis but outside of his normal aggro radius.  He'll tag allong like a lost puppy.  Of cource, he can't have a spawn point.  If it's clearly a rockfiend that has a fixed spawn point and will wander back, this won't work if you let him wander back.  Once mobs reach their spawn points, their hate list is wiped clean and he won't re-aggro if you stand up.</P><P><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26159">Reegor</A> Mortees<BR>scaled Warlock</font></td>
